VV.V.N. Bhargava, disciple of Malladi Suribabu of Vijayawada is a promising Carnatic vocalist. Hailing from a family of musicians, he has regularly been performing at concerts.He holds an M.A. degree in music and is presently doing his M.Phil in music in Telugu University, a faculty that was launched recently. He has ability to maintain the right kind of import of the raaga and sing the kriti with sahitya clarity. He is already a graded artiste of AIR. His concert, under the auspices of Sujanaranjani at Hanuman Devasthanam hall last week, revealed that he will have more concert opportunities coming his way.He was accompanied by Pawan Singh on violin and Vidyasagar on mridangam. He began withSaveri Varnam Sarasudaand went forMahaganapathimin Nata of Diksitar with breezy swaras.Govardhana Gireesamof Dikshitar in Hindolam,Poorayamamakamamof Narayana Teertha, a Tarangam in Bilahari.Poorvikalyani was later essayed in detail and sang in itGjanamosagaradawith nereval and swaram at the lineParamatmudu Jeevatmudu Padunalugu Lokamulakuvividly. The main melody he chose for the concert wasKharaharapriya Kori Sevimpararewith an elaborate nereval and swara kalpana. A rare Subrahmanyena inSuddha Dhanyasi, Koluvaiyunnade inDevagandhari,Entamuddo Yenta Sogasoin Bindumalini were other kirtanas worth mentioning. The young man has clarity in sahitya and has good voice with good range that he used it well for modulation.G.S
